hopobject.body: A few months www.health-science-spirit.com/meridians.html There is, as it happens, confirmatory evidence from animal experiments. As reported in Arthritis and Rheumatism three years ago, administering Prozac to mice with swollen joints resulted in “reduced inflammation, cartilage and bone erosion and preservation of the joint structure”. Prozac is cheaper and better tolerated than most drugs for rheumatological conditions. It would be interesting to hear from others who have had a similar experience.
